I was at a french school before taking the IB program and I got to learn spanish and latin pretty well there, I was almost fluent so it helped me a lot for my IB transition. When went into IB, something that annoyed me was that they were mixing SL and HL classes BOTH years. I don't think that it was the ideal working environment but it still turned out pretty well.

For Spanish we started reviewing after the orals. For English L L we didn't have much review other than looking over the books the last few classes. For math, we were done 2 months early so we did a lot of review. For Econ we were done 2.5 months early, we all did individual presentations covering all subjects. For Physics we had review classes on the week-ends 1 month prior to the exam yet we didnt have time to cover the whole syllabus.
